HEADWORD: fizz
<hw>fizz</hw> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧z)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>fizzed</conjf> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧zd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>fizzing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>f⟦imac⟧sa</ets> to break wind, Dan. <ets>fise</ets> to foist,
fizzle, OSw. <ets>fisa</ets>, G. <ets>fisten</ets>, <ets>feisten</ets>.
Cf. <er>Foist</er>.]</ety> <def>To make a hissing sound, such as that of
a burning fuse or a bubbling carbonated beverage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

